review_blob: PLEASE take into account that you will not find this on tap in most pubs in Aus and most consider this beer as Australian as Greg Norman or Kylie Minogue (they may ahve originated here but they both left a LONG time ago and we dont want em back).
Malty and caramel. Has the coopers nose about it, quite nice but expensive.

bit of coffee flavour and not creamy.

Like a 50 with this one (half t old, half t new)

One of the better mass produced draughts, anything is better than VB.

Something to drink at the pub, probably an emotional attachment after all these years.

Goes well as 50 (half tooheys new, half tooheys old)

I dont mind this although it is has a bit of a chemical taste in there.

Goes down pretty easy, doesnt offend or set the world on fire

I actually like their pale better which is different to most.

Wheaty flavour and a bit fruity, refreshing and easy on a hot day.

Cloudy with sediment in the bottled variety.

A bit sweet and fruity and extremely easy to drink on a hot day. One of my favourites.
A truckload of people rate this and I can see why, quite refreshing. BUT it is just too busy for me, too much like a bottle of perfume.
You can't expect too much from a light.. pretty watery and unexciting. only think about it if you are really thirsty and have to drive
